summary: Bill & Ted 3: Face the Music Announcement Orion Pictures has posted a video of the most excellent Alex Winter and Keanu Reeves...
caption:
Bill & Ted 3: Face the Music Announcement

Orion Pictures has posted a video of the most excellent Alex Winter and Keanu Reeves thanking fans for their support as they might actually get to make Bill & Ted 3: Face the Music. The film finds The Wild Stallions as middle aged men who still haven’t fulfilled their destiny of writing a song that brings harmony to the universe.

Bill & Ted 3: Face the Music is currently scheduled to release on August 21, 2020.

summary: Film Review | John Wick (2014) Some awe-inspiring action sequences in this, with such a simple plot. Doesn’t take much to make...
caption:
Film Review | John Wick (2014)

Some awe-inspiring action sequences in this, with such a simple plot. Doesn’t take much to make something that feels pretty landmark - and relying on Keanu Reeves is coming back in style, it seems.

He crushes it as John Wick - doesn’t need to do much but beat some ass over and over again. The simple call to action makes for such a great inciting action to push him back into his assassin line of work, and the chilling story from Russian mob father to son makes Wick’s boogeyman status all the greater. Top that with an amazing supporting cast of all the most grim men you can think of - and this sucker’s excellent.

54 of 365.

3.5 out of 5.

blog.name: angelofberlin2000
blog.title: Like a Rose trampled on the ground
blog.description:
In addition to the pain and the exhaustion, he recalled how waiting on the cross between takes became tedious. To fight the boredom, he listened to music on headphones. One particular song called "Above All" (Like a Rose ...) by Michael W. Smith helped him through his most difficult moments.

"It arrived when I was confused and angry. I didn't think I could go on. The song described how Jesus was rejected and alone. That thought took me to a place — it opened an interior door that held me while on the cross," an emotional Caviezel explained. "The experience of feeling rejected and alone as all those around me laughed while drinking their hot coffees, oblivious to what was occurring. Jesus must have felt like this — forsaken, rejected, alone, and despised. It helped me pray in a very deep way — to pray without words, to pray from the heart. The discomfort, the loneliness, the split shoulder, the raw flesh all forced me into the arms of God because I had nowhere else to go for a performance I knew I was unable to create."
Jim Caviezel, Shamelessly Catholic
